<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900806-0039</DOCNO><DOCID>900806-0039.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Diasonics Inc.:   Company Settles Dispute   With Toshiba Unit on Sale</HL><DATE>07/11/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B8</SO><CO>   DIA J.TOS</CO><IN>TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)MEDICAL SUPPLIES (MDS)</IN><LP>   Diasonics Inc. said it settled a dispute with a ToshibaCorp. unit over the final sale price to Toshiba of Diasonic'sultrasound business.   Under the agreement, the Toshiba unit will pay Diasonicsan additional $13.5 million, Diasonics said in Milipitas,Calif.</LP><TEXT>   Diasonics completed the sale of its MRI division toToshiba America Medical Systems Inc. last November for $167.5million plus the assumption of certain debt. But in FebruaryDiasonics asked Toshiba for an additional $23 million toreflect certain equity changes in the division prior to thesale's closing date. The Toshiba unit balked, insteaddemanding a $19 million refund from Diasonics.   The accord resolves the disputes outstanding with Toshiba,a Diasonics official said. Diasonics' stock closed at$3.3125, down 18.75 cents, on the American Stock Exchange.The company disclosed the accord after the close of tradingyesterday.   ---   Corrections andamp; Amplifications                                                                                                          DIASONICS Inc. sold its magnetic resonance imagingbusiness to a Toshiba Corp. unit. In the July 11 edition, thebusiness that Diasonics sold was misidentified.   (WSJ Aug. 6, 1990)</TEXT></DOC>